SIMPLE: unseat
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unseat
<hw>Un*seat"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>seat</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To throw from one's seat; to deprive of a
seat.</def> <rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Specifically, to deprive of the right to sit in a
legislative body, as for fraud in election.</def>
<rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1581 -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unseconded</ent>⟦br⟧
